quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,"Doth he not know, therefore, when that which is in the graves shall be taken forth"
  100,10,and that which is in men's breasts shall be brought to light
  100,11,"that their Lord will, on that day, be fully informed concerning them"
  101,1,The striking
  101,2,What is the striking
  101,3,And what shall make thee to understand how terrible the striking will be
  101,4,On that day men shall be like moths scattered abroad
  101,5,and the mountains shall become like carded wool of various colours driven by the wind
  101,6,Moreover he whose balance shall be heavy with good works
  101,7,shall lead a pleasing life
  101,8,But as to him whose balance shall be light
  101,9,his dwelling shall be the pit of hell
  101,10,What shall make thee to understand how frightful the pit of hell is
  101,11,It is a burning fire
  102,1,The emulous desire of multiplying riches and children employeth you
  102,2,until ye visit the graves
  102,3,"By no means should ye thus employ your time: Hereafter shall ye know your folly"
  102,4,"Again, by no means: Hereafter shall ye know your folly"
  102,5,"By no means: If ye knew the consequence hereof with certainty of knowledge, ye would not act thus"
  102,6,Verily ye shall see hell
  102,7,"Again, ye shall surely see it with the eye of certainty"
  102,8,"Then shall ye be examined, on that day, concerning the pleasures with which ye have amused yourselves in this life"
  103,1,By the afternoon
  103,2,verily man employeth himself in that which will prove of loss
  103,3,"Except those who believe, and do that which is right; and who mutually recommend the truth, and mutually recommend perseverance unto each other"
  104,1,"Woe unto every slanderer, and backbiter"
  104,2,"Who heapeth up riches, and prepareth the same for the time to come"
  104,3,He thinketh that his riches will render him immortal
  104,4,By no means. He shall surely be cast into al Hotama
  104,5,And what shall cause thee to understand what al Hotama is
  104,6,It is the kindled fire of God
  104,7,which shall mount above the hearts of those who shall be cast therein
  104,8,Verily it shall be as an arched vault above them
  104,9,on columns of vast extent
  105,1,Hast thou not seen how thy Lord dealt with the masters of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their treacherous design an occasion of drawing them into error
  105,3,and send against them flocks of birds
  105,4,which cast down upon them stones of baked clay
  105,5,and render them like the leaves of corn eaten by cattle
  106,1,For the uniting of the tribe of Koreish
  106,2,their uniting in sending forth the caravan of merchants and purveyors in winter and summer
  106,3,Let them serve the Lord of this house
  106,4,"who supplieth them with food against hunger, and hath rendered them secure from fear"
  107,1,What thinkest thou of him who denieth the future judgment as a falsehood
  107,2,It is he who pusheth away the orphan
  107,3,and stirreth not up others to feed the poor
  107,4,Woe be unto those who pray
  107,5,and who are negligent at their prayer
  107,6,who play the hypocrites
  107,7,and deny necessaries to the needy
  108,1,Verily we have given thee al Cawthar
  108,2,"Wherefore pray unto thy Lord, and slay the victims"
  108,3,verily he who hateth thee shall be childless
  109,1,"Say: O unbelievers"
  109,2,I will not worship that which ye worship
  109,3,nor will ye worship that which I worship
  109,4,Neither do I worship that which ye worship
  109,5,neither do ye worship that which I worship
  109,6,"Ye have your religion, and I my religion"
  110,1,"When the assistance of God shall come, and the victory"
  110,2,and thou shalt see the people enter into the religion of God by troops
  110,3,"Celebrate the praise of thy Lord, and ask pardon of Him; for He is inclined to forgive"
  111,1,"The hands of Abu Laheb shall perish, and he shall perish"
  111,2,"His riches shall not profit him, neither that which he hath gained"
  111,3,He shall go down to be burned into flaming fire
  111,4,"and his wife also, bearing wood"
  111,5,having on her neck a cord of twisted fibres of a palm-tree
  112,1,"Say, God is one God"
  112,2,the eternal God
  112,3,"He begetteth not, neither is He begotten"
  112,4,And there is not any one like unto Him
  113,1,"Say, I fly for refuge unto the Lord of the day-break"
  113,2,that He may deliver me from the mischief of those things which He hath created
  113,3,"and from the mischief of the night, when it cometh on"
  113,4,and from the mischief of women blowing on knots
  113,5,"and from the mischief of the envious, when he envieth"
  114,1,"Say, I fly for refuge unto the Lord of men"
  114,2,the King of men
  114,3,the God of men
  114,4,that He may deliver me from the mischief of the whisperer who slyly withdraweth
  114,5,who whispereth evil suggestions into the breasts of men
  114,6,from genii and men